I have the same problem (as everyone else), and for me, it's clearly a P2 ou P1 error, and not related to TextFormField but to TextField component.

As a very ugly temporary work arround, you can play with FocusNode  and some timers.

You can extend FocusNode:

```dart
import 'package:easy_debounce/easy_debounce.dart';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:loggy/loggy.dart';

class FocusNodeExt extends FocusNode {
  FocusNodeExt({
    super.debugLabel,
    super.onKey,
    super.onKeyEvent,
    super.skipTraversal = false,
    super.canRequestFocus = true,
    super.descendantsAreFocusable = true,
    super.descendantsAreTraversable = true,
  }) {
    _debounceLabel = 'focus$hashCode';
    addListener(_onFocusChanged);
  }

  late final String _debounceLabel;

  void _onFocusChanged() {
    logDebug("_onFocusChanged");
    if (hasFocus) {
      logDebug("hasFocus");

      EasyDebounce.debounce(
          _debounceLabel, // <-- An ID for this particular debouncer
          const Duration(seconds: 20), // <-- The debounce duration
          () {
        logDebug("ask lost focus");
        unfocus();
      });
    } else {
      logDebug("Cancel deb");
      EasyDebounce.cancel(_debounceLabel);
    }
  }

  void resetCancelTimer() {
    logDebug("reset deb");
    _onFocusChanged();
  }
}
```

Then inside your  widget:

```dart
...
  final FocusNodeExt focusNode = FocusNodeExt();
  final TextEditingController searchTextController = TextEditingController();
    searchTextController.addListener(() {
      focusNode.resetCancelTimer();
});
...
TextField(focusNode: focusNode,
controller: searchTextController,
...);

it's far from perfect, but this prevents the draining of the user's battery.

I couldn't reproduce it wIth iPhone 7 iOS 13.5.
Who can test with iOS 11-12 - check https://fltf.netlify.app/ - built with provided code sample with current master `1.19.0-2.0.pre.193`.

