I am still facing this issue on iOS 16.1 and flutter 3.3.6.

When tapping korean content `onChanged` call is triggered many time with empty value. I think it is because the engine need some time to "build" the final korean letter.

This issue is quite bothering when trying to setup an autocompletion for search for example.

I managed to find a hacky fix, that requires to use an `EditingController` :

```dart
TextFormField(
  controller: controller,
  onChanged: (val) async {
    // https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/50163
    // because of this issue, `onChanged` is called multiple times when tapping korean content
    // this issue is caused by korean symbol position being changed on every new symbol
    // e.g tapping (ㄱ → 가 → 강) calls `onChanged` 6 times (ㄱ → '' → 가 → '' → 강)
    // adding some time for the engine to build the korean letter fix the issue
    await Future.delayed(const Duration(milliseconds: 10));

    // ignore skipped empty `val`
    if (val != controller.text) return;

    if (onChanged != null) {
      return onChanged!(controller.text);
    }
  },
)
```

hopefully it can helps some people facing this issue.

